\n\n\n\nWhat is AMIC?The Asian Media Information and Communication Centre (AMIC)\xc2\xa0is an international, non-profit, non-government organization that serves as a regional research hub for media and communication issues.\xc2\xa0Based in Manila, Philippines, it was established in 1971 to encourage ethical and social responsibility of the media to support democratic access and participation in media development and production.\xc2\xa0AMIC also works to provide opportunities for empowerment of disadvantaged sectors in the communication/media environments in developing countries in Asia.\n\n \n \n\n\nRead More\n\n \n\nBecome an AMIC Member\n\n \n\nJoin the AMIC Consortium\n\n \n \n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n\nList of Institutional Members\n \n \n \n\n\n\nUniversity of Pennsylvania\nAbout University of Pennsylvania \n \nDe la Salle University Dasmarinas (DLSD) - Communication and Journalism Department\nAbout De la Salle University Dasmarinas (DLSD)  \n \nUniversity of Santo Tomas (UST) - Department of Communication\nAbout University of Santo Tomas (UST) \n \nUniversity of the Philippines @ LOS BANOS - College of Development Communication (UPLB-CDC)\nAbout University of the Philippines Los Ba\xc3\xb1os \n \n Holy Angel University (HAU) - Department of Communication\nAbout Holy Angel University (HAU) \n \nGruppo Agatep, Inc.\nAbout Gruppo Agatep, Inc.) \n \nUniversity of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB)\nAbout University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB) \n \nSukhothai Thammathirat Open University (STOU)\nAbout Sukhothai Thammathirat Open University (STOU) \n \n \n\xa0\n \n \n\n\nPolytechnic University of the Philippines (PUP) - College of Communication\nAbout Polytechnic University of the Philippines (PUP) \n \nFar Eastern University (FEU) - Department of Communication\nAbout Far Eastern University (FEU) \n \nManipal Academy of Higher Education\n Manipal Academy of Higher Education (Deemed to be University) \n \nManipal University, Dubai\nAbout Manipal University, Dubai \n \nPhilippine Women\xe2\x80\x99s University (PWU) - College of Arts and Sciences\nAbout Philippine Women\xe2\x80\x99s University (PWU) \n \nCentro Escolar University (CEU)\nAbout Centro Escolar University (CEU) \n \nBicol State University - College of Arts and Letters\nAbout Bicol State University \n \nMudhra Institute of Communication Ahmedabad (MICA)\nMudhra Institute of Communication Ahmedabad (MICA) \n \nUniversity of Macau\nAbout University of Macau \n \n \n \n \n \n\n\n\nAMIC Journals\n \n \n \n\n\n\n\n \n\nAsian Journal of CommunicationPrint ISSN:\xc2\xa00129-2986\xc2\xa0Online ISSN:\xc2\xa01742-0911\n \nLaunched in 1990, Asian Journal of Communication (AJC) is a refereed international publication that provides a venue for high-quality communication scholarship with an Asian focus and perspectives from the region. We aim to highlight research on the systems and processes of communication in the Asia-Pacific region and among Asian communities around the world to a wide international audience. It publishes articles that report empirical studies, develop communication theory, and enhance research methodology.\nAJC is accepted by and listed in the Social Science Citation Index (SSCI) published by Clarivate Analytics. The journal is housed editorially at the\xc2\xa0Wee Kim Wee School of Communication and Information\xc2\xa0at Nanyang Technological University in Singapore, jointly with the\xc2\xa0AMIC\n \n \n \n \n\n\n\nMedia AsiaPrint ISSN:\xc2\xa00129-6612\xc2\xa0Online ISSN:\xc2\xa02377-6277\n \nPublished since 1974,\xc2\xa0Media Asia\xc2\xa0is a scholarly journal that\xc2\xa0shares research-based findings and\xc2\xa0critical insights addressing contemporary media issues and communication challenges in Asia. The journal welcomes articles in either the social scientific or humanistic tradition and in any disciplinary orientation. Research articles are double-blind reviewed. In addition to publishing completed research,\xc2\xa0Media Asia\xc2\xa0also includes essays and opinion pieces for academics and practitioners to share ideas and help shape the agenda for communication scholarship, practice and policy.\nMedia Asia\xc2\xa0is a journal of the\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0Asian Media Information and Communication Centre (AMIC). It is housed editorially at Hong Kong Baptist University\xe2\x80\x99s\xc2\xa0Centre for Media and Communication Research.\n \n \n\n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n\nAMIC Socials\n \nPowered by Curator.io\n\n\n \n \n \n  \n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n\n\nPrivacy Policy\nDisclaimer\n \n \n\n\n\n\n\nFacebook\n\n\n\n\nTwitter\n\n\n\n\nGoogle\n\n\n\n\nInstagram\n\n\n\n\nRSS\n\n\nDesigned by Elegant Themes | Powered by WordPress  \n\n \n \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n'